        "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/5/1",
        "text": [
          " : سُئِلَ أَبُو عَبْدِ اَللَّهِ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ عَنْ قَاضٍ بَيْنَ قَرْيَتَيْنِ يَأْخُذُ مِنَ اَلسُّلْطَانِ عَلَى اَلْقَضَاءِ اَلرِّزْقَ فَقَالَ \"ذَاكَ سُحْتٌ\"."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
            "Hadith.3227 - Al-Hasan ibn Mahbub narrated from Abdullah ibn Sinan who said:\nAbu Abdillah (as) was asked about a judge between two villages who takes a salary from the ruler for judging.\nImam (as) said: \"That is unlawful (suht).\""
          ]
        }
      }
